Officl Navy Photo of Admiral Mitscher plaque,5/28/62.

Plaque reads,

&quot;Admiral Marc Andrew Mitscher United States Navy. His was strength without conceit; Courage fortified with comprehension; Leadership tempered with tolerance. One of the first to assess the great potential of Naval Aviation, he fought unceasingly for its progressive development. In World War II Admiral Mitscher demostrated to our enemies, our allies, and to the world the tremendous force of carrier air power, superbly led and expertly operated. Presented by shipmates and friends. 1955&quot;
